<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 18 at 2:48AM EST  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...Slick Travel Conditions Saturday Morning...
Wet snow is expected to develop and could mix with sleet and
freezing rain at times. Slushy snow accumulations of a couple
inches could cause roads to become slick. The heavier snow will
diminish by mid morning, but lighter snow showers or freezing
drizzle could continue into early afternoon. Extra time may be
needed to reach your destination if you are traveling Saturday
morning, and remember to take it slow in ice and snow.</description>
